newsitem.title: USA: US West Coast gasoline drops ahead of NYMEX expiry.
newsitem.headline: US West Coast gasoline drops ahead of NYMEX expiry.

text.p: U.S. West Coast gasoline prices eased with sharply lower gasoline futures early Monday, ahead of the contract's expiry.
NYMEX unleaded gasoline futures closed at 62.20 cents a gallon, down 2.40 cents from Friday as traders exited their front-month positions.
Traders remained unclear about which Bay-area refinery experienced problems last Friday, with Tosco's Martinez, Calif., facility and Unocal's Rodeo plant rumored in trouble.
One trader said a hydrogen-related unit might be disrupted at Unocal's Rodeo refinery.
